HEADWORD: Proximity
<hw>Prox*im"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proximitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>proximit⟦eacute⟧</ets> See
<er>Proximate</er>, and cf. <er>Propinquity</er>,
<er>Approach</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being next in
time, place, causation, influence, etc.; immediate nearness, either in
place, blood, or alliance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If he plead <qex>proximity</qex> of blood⟦br⟧
That empty title is with ease withstood.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proximo</ent>⟦br⟧
